  "title": "Plant Manager (O&G / Aviation) - East",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br /></p><ul><li>Plan, organize, and run day-to-day plant operations to consistently meet or exceed customer expectations on output, quality, and on-time delivery.</li><li>Drive continuous improvement initiatives across productivity, digitalisation, and operational excellence to meet and exceed targets.</li><li>Increase production capacity, asset utilization, and operational flexibility while minimizing costs, controlling overtime, and maintaining quality standards</li><li>Own business performance including production output, sales revenue plans, operating profit targets, and overall cost management.</li><li>Allocate human resources effectively, fully utilize assets, delegate accountability, and build a high-performing, engaged team with strong retention</li><li>Implement strategies aligned with corporate initiatives and participate in regional and global operational reviews </li><li> Champion plant safety and compliance</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong><br /></p><ul><li>Degree in Engineering</li><li>At least 10 years of experince in Oil and Gas / Aviation Manufacturing</li><li>Strong Leadership</li><li>Location: East </li></ul><p><br />Account Manager:<br />Kerwin Tan Kai Bin (R1331624)<br />kerwin.tan@searchasia.com.sg<br />EA16S8107</p>",
